div.p: Currently, the implementation uses the handlebars.java library instead of Gemma. The reasons were relatively complex modifications on Gemma.

Unfortunately, Handlebars brings it own problems, as it forgets about quotes around strings and it's API is aligned to the javascript API, which results in an unclear API where a lot of parameters are Java Objects without any further specification about the needs of this type. Therefore, Gemma is considered again for further improvements.
